import seaborn as sns

def plot_var(col_name, full_name, continuous):
    """
    Visualize a variable with and without faceting on the loan status.
    - col_name is the variable name in the dataframe
    - full_name is the full variable name
    - continuous is True if the variable is continuous, False otherwise
    """
    f, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(12,3), dpi=90)
    
    # Plot without loan status
    if continuous:
        sns.histplot(data.loc[data[col_name].notnull(), col_name], kde=False, ax=ax1)
    else:
        sns.countplot(data[col_name], order=sorted(data[col_name].unique()), color='#5975A4', saturation=1, ax=ax1)
    ax1.set_xlabel(full_name)
    ax1.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax1.set_title(full_name)

    # Plot with loan status
    if continuous:
        sns.boxplot(x=col_name, y='loan_status', data=data, ax=ax2)
        ax2.set_ylabel('')
        ax2.set_title(full_name + ' by Loan Status')
    else:
        charge_off_rates = data.groupby(col_name)['loan_status'].value_counts(normalize=True).loc[:,'Charged Off']
        sns.barplot(x=charge_off_rates.index, y=charge_off_rates.values, color='#5975A4', saturation=1, ax=ax2)
        ax2.set_ylabel('Fraction of Loans Charged-off')
        ax2.set_title('Charge-off Rate by ' + full_name)
    ax2.set_xlabel(full_name)
    
    plt.tight_layout()

import lightgbm as lgb
from lightgbm import early_stopping, log_evaluation, record_evaluation
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.metrics import (
    roc_auc_score, average_precision_score,
    precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,
    confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay,
    roc_curve, precision_recall_curve,
    log_loss
)

# LightGBM Dataset 
dtrain_40 = lgb.Dataset(X_train, label=y_train)
dvalid_40 = lgb.Dataset(X_test, label=y_test)

#   ( 40)
best_params_40 = {
    "objective": "binary",
    "metric": ["auc", "binary_logloss"],  #  
    "verbosity": -1,
    "boosting_type": "gbdt",
    "n_jobs": -1,
    "feature_pre_filter": False,
    "lambda_l1": 0.0,
    "lambda_l2": 0.0,
    "num_leaves": 31,
    "feature_fraction": 0.4,
    "bagging_fraction": 1.0,
    "bagging_freq": 0,
    "min_child_samples": 20,
}

evals_result_40 = {}  #  

model_40 = lgb.train(
    best_params_40,
    train_set=dtrain_40,
    valid_sets=[dtrain_40, dvalid_40],
    valid_names=['train', 'valid'],
    num_boost_round=1000,
    callbacks=[
        early_stopping(stopping_rounds=50),
        log_evaluation(period=100),
        record_evaluation(evals_result_40)  #     
    ]
)

#    ()
y_pred_prob_40 = model_40.predict(X_test)

#   (threshold=0.5)
y_pred_40 = (y_pred_prob_40 >= 0.5).astype(int)

#    
roc_auc_40 = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_prob_40)
pr_auc_40 = average_precision_score(y_test, y_pred_prob_40)
precision_40 = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_40)
recall_40 = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_40)
f1_40 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_40)
cm_40 = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_40)

print(f" Test ROC AUC (roc_auc_40): {roc_auc_40:.4f}")
print(f" Test PR AUC (pr_auc_40): {pr_auc_40:.4f}")
print(f" Test Precision (precision_40): {precision_40:.4f}")
print(f" Test Recall (recall_40): {recall_40:.4f}")
print(f" Test F1 Score (f1_40): {f1_40:.4f}")
print("\n Confusion Matrix (cm_40):")
print(pd.DataFrame(
    cm_40,
    columns=['Predicted Neg', 'Predicted Pos'],
    index=['Actual Neg', 'Actual Pos']
))

# Confusion Matrix 
disp_40 = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm_40)
disp_40.plot(cmap="Blues")
plt.title("Confusion Matrix (Test Set)")
plt.show()

# ROC Curve 
fpr_40, tpr_40, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob_40)
plt.plot(fpr_40, tpr_40, label=f"ROC AUC = {roc_auc_40:.4f}")
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
plt.xlabel("False Positive Rate")
plt.ylabel("True Positive Rate")
plt.title("ROC Curve (Test Set)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Precision-Recall Curve 
prec_40, rec_40, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob_40)
plt.plot(rec_40, prec_40, label=f"PR AUC = {pr_auc_40:.4f}")
plt.xlabel("Recall")
plt.ylabel("Precision")
plt.title("Precision-Recall Curve (Test Set)")
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

%matplotlib inline

import time
import lightgbm as lgb
from lightgbm import early_stopping, log_evaluation, record_evaluation
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.metrics import (
    roc_auc_score, average_precision_score,
    precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,
    confusion_matrix, ConfusionMatrixDisplay,
    roc_curve, precision_recall_curve,
)
import shap
from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer

# --    --
# X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test     .

# 1.   
imputer = SimpleImputer(strategy='mean')
X_train_imputed = imputer.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_imputed = imputer.transform(X_test)

# 2. PCA 
n_components = 50
pca = PCA(n_components=n_components, random_state=42)
X_train_reduced = pca.fit_transform(X_train_imputed)
X_test_reduced = pca.transform(X_test_imputed)

# 3. LightGBM Dataset 
dtrain = lgb.Dataset(X_train_reduced, label=y_train)
dvalid = lgb.Dataset(X_test_reduced, label=y_test)

# 4.  
best_params = {
    "objective": "binary",
    "metric": ["auc", "binary_logloss"],
    "verbosity": -1,
    "boosting_type": "gbdt",
    "n_jobs": -1,
    "feature_pre_filter": False,
    "lambda_l1": 0.0,
    "lambda_l2": 0.0,
    "num_leaves": 31,
    "feature_fraction": 0.4,
    "bagging_fraction": 1.0,
    "bagging_freq": 0,
    "min_child_samples": 20,
}

evals_result_41 = {}

#     (15 = 900)
max_train_seconds = 900

def time_limit_callback(env):
    if not hasattr(time_limit_callback, "start_time"):
        time_limit_callback.start_time = time.time()
    elapsed = time.time() - time_limit_callback.start_time
    if elapsed > max_train_seconds:
        print(f"\n Training stopped after {elapsed:.1f} seconds (time limit reached).")
        raise lgb.callback.EarlyStopException(env.iteration)

# 5.   (   )
model_41 = lgb.train(
    best_params,
    train_set=dtrain,
    valid_sets=[dtrain, dvalid],
    valid_names=['train', 'valid'],
    num_boost_round=1000,
    callbacks=[
        early_stopping(stopping_rounds=50),
        log_evaluation(period=100),
        record_evaluation(evals_result_41),
        time_limit_callback
    ]
)

# 6.     
y_pred_prob_41 = model_41.predict(X_test_reduced)
y_pred_41 = (y_pred_prob_41 >= 0.5).astype(int)

roc_auc_41 = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_prob_41)
pr_auc_41 = average_precision_score(y_test, y_pred_prob_41)
precision_41 = precision_score(y_test, y_pred_41)
recall_41 = recall_score(y_test, y_pred_41)
f1_41 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_41)
cm_41 = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_41)

print(f" Test ROC AUC: {roc_auc_41:.4f}")
print(f" Test PR AUC: {pr_auc_41:.4f}")
print(f" Test Precision: {precision_41:.4f}")
print(f" Test Recall: {recall_41:.4f}")
print(f" Test F1 Score: {f1_41:.4f}")
print("\n Confusion Matrix:")
print(pd.DataFrame(cm_41, columns=['Predicted Neg', 'Predicted Pos'], index=['Actual Neg', 'Actual Pos']))

# 7.  - Confusion Matrix
disp_41 = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(confusion_matrix=cm_41)
disp_41.plot(cmap="Blues")
plt.title("Confusion Matrix (Test Set 41)")
plt.show()

# 8. ROC Curve
fpr_41, tpr_41, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob_41)

plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')

plt.title("Precision-Recall Curve (Test Set 41)")
